column5: Went carping at a local creek mouth today and hooked into a decent sized fish.  I was having some problems getting him in the net with the other hand still on the rod until a helpful angler from down the way came over and assisted. If it's anyone from on here, I thank you kindly.  A pretty clean 33"x24"...still need a scale.
Awesome! Always nice when your in need and someone helps out!  Great fish to btw!!!
What a hog, Dude !!! Thanks for letting us take a peek.
Nice fish! Great to hear a "good news" fishing story!
